net.demilich.metastone.game.cards

Class CardZone

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractList<E>
        • net.demilich.metastone.game.entities.EntityZone<Card>
          • net.demilich.metastone.game.cards.CardZone
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<Card>, java.util.Collection<Card>, java.util.List<Card>, CardList

    public class CardZone
extends EntityZone<Card>
implements CardList
    This class is a CardList that represents the Zones.HAND and Zones.DECK. It is implemented as an EntityZone because it represents an in-game zone; i.e., an entity can only be in one zone at once.
    See Also:
    for a {@link List} that implements {@link CardList} that does not represent a zone in the game and can be used for all sorts of game logic that needs to deal with lists of cards., Serialized Form
